NEWS GOV-MO: University of Macau Awards Honorary Doctorates to Seven Distinguished Individuals. The University of Macau held the "2021 Honorary Degree and Higher Degree Award Ceremony" today (11th), awarding honorary doctorates to Liu Zunyi, Chen Kaixian, Nakamura Shuji, Li Lanjuan, Li Xiaoliang, Zhu Lilan, and Jiang Zhaohui in recognition of their outstanding achievements and significant contributions to the development of society and education. At the award ceremony, the Chief Executive and University of Macau Supervisor representative, Secretary for Social Affairs and Culture, Ouyang Yu, accompanied by Chairman of the University Council Lin Jincheng and President of the University Song Yonghua, presented the honorary doctorates. Professor Liu Zunyi received an Honorary Doctorate in Education, Professor Chen Kaixian an Honorary Doctorate in Science, Professor Nakamura Shuji an Honorary Doctorate in Science, Professor Li Lanjuan an Honorary Doctorate in Science, Professor Li Xiaoliang an Honorary Doctorate in Business Administration, Professor Zhu Lilan an Honorary Doctorate in Science, and Ms. Jiang Zhaohui an Honorary Doctorate in Science. In his speech, Ouyang Yu first extended warm congratulations and high respect to the seven distinguished individuals who were awarded honorary doctorates, noting that they have achieved extraordinary accomplishments in different fields and made outstanding contributions to national development and global progress. At the same time, Ouyang Yu also expressed his heartfelt blessings to the graduates and their parents, as well as his sincere respect for the dedicated and academically accomplished faculty and staff of the university. Professor Sun Yifeng, a visiting professor at the University of Macau's Faculty of Humanities, praised Liu Zunyi during the reading of his commendation, stating that Professor Liu Zunyi is a globally renowned economist known for his outstanding academic achievements and forward-looking educational philosophy. In addition to his accomplishments in economic development, economic growth, and East Asian economics, he is also a visionary educational leader. In short, he has made outstanding contributions in numerous fields. When reading the commendation for Nakamura Shuji, Sun Yifeng stated that Professor Nakamura Shuji is a pioneer in sustainable energy technology. He became one of the three recipients of the 2014 Nobel Prize in Physics for his invention of the blue light-emitting diode (LED). Professor Nakamura's invention not only completely transformed the lighting industry but also promoted the development of white light-emitting diodes, which are now widely used in everyday life and industrial production, making a tremendous contribution to human welfare. When reading the commendation for Li Lanjuan, Sun Yifeng stated that Professor Li Lanjuan, as a pioneer in China's artificial liver field, created the unique and effective Li's Artificial Liver System, which achieved significant breakthroughs in the treatment of severe hepatitis and liver failure, significantly reducing the mortality rate of liver failure. In the fight against the COVID-19 pandemic, her team's proposed "four anti-two balance" strategy and the three major technologies of artificial liver, microecology, and stem cells greatly improved the treatment success rate for severe cases. When reading the commendation for Li Xiaoliang, Sun Yifeng stated that Professor Li Xiaoliang laid the foundation for innovative research in operations management, shaped the way of thinking in supply chain theory and practice, and completely changed business models around the world. Li Xiaoliang is known for popularizing the concept of the bullwhip effect in operations management and exploring measures to address this phenomenon. Nowadays, under the pandemic and tense economic situations, the bullwhip effect has become increasingly prominent, causing severe disruptions in supply chains. Li Xiaoliang's forward-looking research is like timely assistance, helping industries cope with difficulties and bringing tremendous social value. When reading the commendation for Zhu Lilan, Sun Yifeng stated that in her scientific research, she discovered a breakthrough and innovative staining technique for preparing samples, enjoying a high reputation among her domestic and international scientific peers. With her extraordinary scientific achievements, she has been honored with important titles such as a Fellow of the International Eurasian Academy of Sciences, winning her rightful place of high esteem in the global scientific community. When reading the commendation for Chen Kaixian, Chen Xin, acting dean of the University of Macau's Institute of Chinese Medical Sciences, stated that Professor Chen Kaixian has been engaged in pharmaceutical research for over 40 years. His outstanding scientific achievements and significant contributions to the nation, Macau, the University of Macau, and national key laboratories have earned him a lofty international status and reputation. His active promotion of the development of traditional Chinese medicine in Macau and the Greater Bay Area fully reflects his sense of mission in dedicating himself to the national medical development strategy. When reading the commendation for Jiang Zhaohui, Xu Chengzhong, the dean of the Faculty of Science and Technology at the University of Macau, stated that Ms. Jiang Zhaohui has participated in the research and development of significant inventions and patents, with more than 15 inventions and patents related to storage virtualization, navigation, file systems, and power management to date. These inventions are highly practical, widely used, and enhance the convenience of human life. As an accomplished inventor, Ms. Jiang often simplifies complex technology and theory, making them accessible to the general public. Finally, Chen Kaixian, as the representative of the honorary doctorates, read the words of thanks. He was delighted to see that the pharmaceutical industry in Macau and the Greater Bay Area has set a good example: from the establishment of the first national key laboratory for the quality research of Chinese medicine at the University of Macau to the thriving development of traditional Chinese medicine in the Greater Bay Area, the University of Macau has played a significant role in integrating outstanding talents in the field of traditional Chinese medicine in the Greater Bay Area. Furthermore, he believes that the management team at the University of Macau has great vision and foresight. They not only provide fertile ground for students' scientific research in academics but also cultivate and deliver many responsible talents to society. He is honored to have the opportunity to engage in exchanges and cooperation with the University of Macau and sincerely congratulates the university on its achievements in recent years.
